<p id="Par38" class="p">In case the curves intersect in 0 ≤ 
 <italic class="italic">c</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> ≤ 
 <italic class="italic">W</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> and 0 ≤ 
 <italic class="italic">c</italic>
 <sub class="sub">P</sub> ≤ 
 <italic class="italic">W</italic>
 <sub class="sub">P</sub> and the intersection is in the region where the risk for the rich is still positive 
 <inline-formula id="IEq8" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M41" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$C &lt; \frac{W}{{\lambda _{\mathrm{R}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M42" class="math">
    <mi class="mi">C</mi>
    <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq8.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>, we have the two best response functions (Eqs. (
 <xref rid="Equ11" ref-type="" class="xref">11)</xref> and (
 <xref rid="Equ12" ref-type="" class="xref">12)</xref>). The intersection gives the evolutionary stable equilibrium
 <disp-formula id="Equ13" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">13</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M43" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast = \frac{{2W_{\mathrm{R}} - W_{\mathrm{P}}}}{3}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M44" display="block" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo class="mo">-</mo>
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">3</mn>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
